ed-level-shifters-because-auto-direction-sensors-cannot-distinguish-driver-from-pull-up","line":34},{"title":"signal-topology-not-voltage-alone-determines-level-shifter-selection","target":"signal-topology-not-voltage-alone-determines-level-shifter-selection","line":35},{"title":"74hct-buffers-are-purpose-built-3v3-to-5v-level-shifters-for-timing-critical-signals","target":"74hct-buffers-are-purpose-built-3v3-to-5v-level-shifters-for-timing-critical-signals","line":36},{"title":"shields","target":"shields","line":39},{"title":"communication","target":"communication","line":40},{"title":"eda-fundamentals","target":"eda-fundamentals","line":41}],"metadata":{"description":"Active level shifters like the TXS0108E detect a rising edge on either side and fire a brief one-shot pulse that actively drives the opposite rail, replacing the passive RC charge path that caps BSS138 shifters near 400kHz — this is the mechanism that enables 110Mbps push-pull operation on a chip otherwise similar in footprint to a BSS138 module","type":"claim","source":"docs/parts/txs0108e-8-channel-bidirectional-level-shifter-auto-direction.md","confidence":"proven","topics":["[[shields]]","[[communication]]","[[eda-fundamentals]]"],"related_components":["txs0108e-level-shifter","hw-221-level-shifter"]},"task_lines":[],"tasks":{},"codeblock_ranges":[],"key":"knowledge/active-level-shifters-use-one-shot-edge-accelerators-to-drive-rising-edges-breaking-the-bss138-rc-ceiling.md"},"smart_blocks:knowledge/active-level-shifters-use-one-shot-edge-accelerators-to-drive-rising-edges-breaking-the-bss138-rc-ceiling.md#---frontmatter---": {"path":null,"last_embed":{"hash":"1vhvhnd","at":1776206993204},"embeddings":{"TaylorAI/bge-micro-v2":{"vec":[-0.11674364,-0.00156661,0.00995752,-0.00154454,-0.04167073,0.0111112,0.02308112,0.05658709,-0.01760177,0.00922031,0.03222933,-0.03826964,0.0195953,-0.01793445,0.02504212,0.00412074,-0.0055677,-0.0104102,0.06112362,0.05481418,0.06071116,-0.03402281,0.03426091,-0.021781